in life after life.

00:00:19.710 --> 00:00:21.864 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, what do you
think happens when you die?

00:00:21.864 --> 00:00:27.550 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that you go to heaven
and that the Lord accepts you.

00:00:27.550 --> 00:00:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And your body's
still here on Earth,

00:00:29.440 --> 00:00:31.090 align:middle line:90%
but your soul is up in heaven.

00:00:31.090 --> 00:00:33.495 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you think
happens when you die?

00:00:33.495 --> 00:00:37.300 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't believe in life
after death necessarily.

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:40.000 align:middle line:84%
I do think there's a
lot we don't understand.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Is there life after life?

00:00:42.460 --> 00:00:46.030 align:middle line:84%
I really don't feel that there's
any way that we could possibly

00:00:46.030 --> 00:00:47.560 align:middle line:90%
know until we're there.

00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:51.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, I definitely believe
that our soul is a very

00:00:51.610 --> 00:00:55.143 align:middle line:90%
powerful emotional thing.

00:00:55.143 --> 00:00:56.560 align:middle line:84%
And I just can't
believe that when

00:00:56.560 --> 00:00:58.420 align:middle line:84%
our body dies that
that's the end.

00:00:58.420 --> 00:01:00.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you believe
in life after life?

00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:01.188 align:middle line:90%
>> I do, yeah.

00:01:01.188 --> 00:01:02.730 align:middle line:84%
I've had a lot of
family members that

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:07.535 align:middle line:84%
have had experiences with people
coming back after they've died.

00:01:07.535 --> 00:01:08.930 align:middle line:90%
So yeah, I do.

00:01:08.930 --> 00:01:12.220 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you think the
nature of the afterlife is?

00:01:12.220 --> 00:01:13.240 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm not sure.

00:01:13.240 --> 00:01:17.647 align:middle line:84%
I feel like people, maybe
their spirits still exist

00:01:17.647 --> 00:01:20.521 align:middle line:84%
and they're just kind of
with the people they love.

00:01:20.521 --> 00:01:22.916 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:22.916 --> 00:01:23.880 align:middle line:90%


00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:26.390 align:middle line:84%
>> There are a
million ways to die.

00:01:26.390 --> 00:01:28.350 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps two million.

00:01:28.350 --> 00:01:30.110 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps even more.

00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:34.760 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we don't even know
how many ways there are to die.

00:01:34.760 --> 00:01:37.550 align:middle line:84%
But one thing we do know
is that a high percentage

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:40.220 align:middle line:84%
of those who die have
what is commonly known

00:01:40.220 --> 00:01:43.560 align:middle line:90%
as a near-death experience.

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.900 align:middle line:84%
Many people report
going up a tunnel

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:50.250 align:middle line:84%
and seeing heavenly bodies
bathed in bright light.

00:01:50.250 --> 00:01:52.260 align:middle line:84%
And a good number
see their life flash

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:54.900 align:middle line:84%
before them in a life
review, and even enter

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:58.360 align:middle line:90%
a heavenly realm.

00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:01.360 align:middle line:84%
We have many representations
of near-death experiences

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:02.940 align:middle line:90%
all around us.

00:02:02.940 --> 00:02:06.100 align:middle line:84%
Artists down through
history and in every culture

00:02:06.100 --> 00:02:09.970 align:middle line:84%
have been there to record
these heavenly encounters.

00:02:09.970 --> 00:02:13.000 align:middle line:84%
It's as though mankind takes
a common path to heaven

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:16.010 align:middle line:90%
and always has.

00:02:16.010 --> 00:02:17.930 align:middle line:84%
I know all about
near-death experiences

00:02:17.930 --> 00:02:21.230 align:middle line:84%
because I have written about
them, nine books and all,

00:02:21.230 --> 00:02:24.510 align:middle line:84%
with a number of the
field's top researchers.

00:02:24.510 --> 00:02:29.330 align:middle line:84%
I have looked at death in many
ways and in many cultures.

00:02:29.330 --> 00:02:32.060 align:middle line:84%
Yet, funny thing,
in all the years

00:02:32.060 --> 00:02:34.430 align:middle line:84%
I have studied and
written about death,

00:02:34.430 --> 00:02:37.640 align:middle line:84%
I have rarely thought that
it would ever happen to me.

00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:39.800 align:middle line:84%
Most of the time I thought
that I would always

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:44.030 align:middle line:84%
be here, a permanent
inhabitant of the living world.

00:02:44.030 --> 00:02:46.190 align:middle line:90%
What was it Sigmund Freud said?

00:02:46.190 --> 00:02:48.380 align:middle line:84%
"When we attempt
to imagine death,

00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:51.590 align:middle line:84%
we perceive ourselves
as spectators."

00:02:51.590 --> 00:02:56.510 align:middle line:84%
Like most everyone else, I, too,
imagined myself as a spectator.

00:02:56.510 --> 00:03:00.360 align:middle line:84%
I hid behind my writing,
safe from mortality.

00:03:00.360 --> 00:03:04.640 align:middle line:84%
I had a box seat in the stadium
of mankind, an eternal observer

00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:07.460 align:middle line:90%
in the game of life.

00:03:07.460 --> 00:03:10.880 align:middle line:90%
Then reality paid me a visit.

00:03:10.880 --> 00:03:14.900 align:middle line:84%
It was a beautiful day with
spectacular light and clean air

00:03:14.900 --> 00:03:19.040 align:middle line:84%
it was, as they say,
a good day to die.

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:21.950 align:middle line:84%
I was out taking a walk
in the desert, when

00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:25.580 align:middle line:84%
out of nowhere, my heart
began to race fast and hard

00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:27.470 align:middle line:90%
like a runaway engine.

00:03:27.470 --> 00:03:30.500 align:middle line:90%
Before long, I was down and out.

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:33.680 align:middle line:84%
In a lucid moment, I realized
that I could easily become

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.900 align:middle line:90%
the subject of my own work.

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:38.390 align:middle line:84%
I imagined what that would
be like by remembering

00:03:38.390 --> 00:03:41.330 align:middle line:84%
stories used in the
books I had written.

00:03:41.330 --> 00:03:43.730 align:middle line:84%
No longer did I believe
that the only thing

00:03:43.730 --> 00:03:47.275 align:middle line:84%
wrong with immortality was
that it goes on forever

00:03:47.275 --> 00:03:50.490 align:middle line:84%
or that it was a fate
worse than death.

00:03:50.490 --> 00:03:54.280 align:middle line:84%
I wanted real answers to
the age old question--

00:03:54.280 --> 00:03:57.840 align:middle line:90%
what happens when we die?

00:03:57.840 --> 00:04:01.620 align:middle line:84%
I decided to go to people who
knew firsthand what happens--

00:04:01.620 --> 00:04:03.810 align:middle line:90%
near-death experiencers.

00:04:03.810 --> 00:04:06.180 align:middle line:84%
Accidents or illness
had brought these people

00:04:06.180 --> 00:04:07.920 align:middle line:90%
to the brink of death.

00:04:07.920 --> 00:04:09.810 align:middle line:84%
They had looked
down into the abyss

00:04:09.810 --> 00:04:13.980 align:middle line:84%
and found it to be, well,
quite pleasant actually.

00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:18.240 align:middle line:84%
If not, why were they
laughing all the time?

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:21.180 align:middle line:84%
I also went to researchers
who had analyzed thousands

00:04:21.180 --> 00:04:23.490 align:middle line:84%
of these near-death
experiences and who

00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:27.600 align:middle line:84%
had come up with some amazing
conclusions about God, heaven,

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:29.130 align:middle line:90%
and the afterlife.

00:04:29.130 --> 00:04:31.770 align:middle line:84%
These were guys I had
written books with.

00:04:31.770 --> 00:04:33.310 align:middle line:90%
Funny, isn't it?

00:04:33.310 --> 00:04:35.070 align:middle line:84%
I always thought I was
writing those books

00:04:35.070 --> 00:04:38.040 align:middle line:90%
for other people, not myself.

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:40.530 align:middle line:10%
And then I talked to
people all over the country

00:04:40.530 --> 00:04:43.470 align:middle line:10%
and from all walks
of life just to see

00:04:43.470 --> 00:04:45.060 align:middle line:10%
what the person on
the street thought

00:04:45.060 --> 00:04:47.550 align:middle line:10%
about death and the hereafter.

00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:50.940 align:middle line:84%
Their answers were proof that
I was not the only one thinking

00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:53.890 align:middle line:90%
about the big question.

00:04:53.890 --> 00:04:59.320 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't really believe in any
kind of afterlife of any kind.

00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:02.100 align:middle line:84%
I think when you die,
you go back to wherever

00:05:02.100 --> 00:05:04.950 align:middle line:90%
you were before you were born.

00:05:04.950 --> 00:05:08.047 align:middle line:90%
>> I hope that you go to heaven.

00:05:08.047 --> 00:05:08.880 align:middle line:90%
I think that you do.

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:10.547 align:middle line:84%
I never thought there
was anything wrong

00:05:10.547 --> 00:05:12.810 align:middle line:84%
with just at least believing
that you go to heaven.

00:05:12.810 --> 00:05:14.560 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to
do you any harm.

00:05:14.560 --> 00:05:15.610 align:middle line:90%
So I hope so.

00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:16.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:16.410 --> 00:05:19.310 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think that we're
spiritual beings that

00:05:19.310 --> 00:05:22.050 align:middle line:84%
have existed before this time
and exists beyond this time,

00:05:22.050 --> 00:05:25.110 align:middle line:84%
and this just
happens to be where

00:05:25.110 --> 00:05:27.728 align:middle line:90%
we're most aware of right now.

00:05:27.728 --> 00:05:30.270 align:middle line:84%
>> I really don't agree with
the whole life after death thing

00:05:30.270 --> 00:05:33.150 align:middle line:84%
because if it really
was life after death,

00:05:33.150 --> 00:05:35.340 align:middle line:84%
what's the point of
even being alive?

00:05:35.340 --> 00:05:38.130 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that there's
some sort of afterlife.

00:05:38.130 --> 00:05:40.530 align:middle line:90%
Your spirit goes somewhere.

00:05:40.530 --> 00:05:42.864 align:middle line:90%
Honestly, I don't know really.

00:05:42.864 --> 00:05:47.292 align:middle line:90%


00:05:47.292 --> 00:05:49.752 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:49.752 --> 00:05:58.130 align:middle line:90%


00:05:58.130 --> 00:06:01.100 align:middle line:10%
>> In order to get a modern
day impression of this subject,

00:06:01.100 --> 00:06:04.220 align:middle line:10%
it is best to spend time with
the scientists who are studying

00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:06.260 align:middle line:10%
this phenomena now.

00:06:06.260 --> 00:06:08.390 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps the best
scientific work is

00:06:08.390 --> 00:06:11.450 align:middle line:90%
being done by Dr. Jeffrey Long.

00:06:11.450 --> 00:06:14.660 align:middle line:84%
We co-wrote the book "Evidence
of the Afterlife," which

00:06:14.660 --> 00:06:17.300 align:middle line:84%
is filled with his
astounding findings

00:06:17.300 --> 00:06:19.880 align:middle line:90%
about death and the beyond.

00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:22.130 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I did say beyond.

00:06:22.130 --> 00:06:26.060 align:middle line:84%
As the founder of the Near-death
Experience Research Foundation,

00:06:26.060 --> 00:06:28.730 align:middle line:84%
also known as
NDERF, Dr. Long has

00:06:28.730 --> 00:06:31.730 align:middle line:84%
investigated thousands of
near-death experience case

00:06:31.730 --> 00:06:33.980 align:middle line:90%
studies worldwide.

00:06:33.980 --> 00:06:35.450 align:middle line:90%
His conclusion?

00:06:35.450 --> 00:06:38.300 align:middle line:84%
There is most
definitely an afterlife.

00:06:38.300 --> 00:06:41.720 align:middle line:10%
>> The question, that really
important question of what

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:45.200 align:middle line:10%
happens when we die, I certainly
have my opinion and have not

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:46.950 align:middle line:10%
been shy about
sharing that opinion.

00:06:46.950 --> 00:06:49.400 align:middle line:84%
I think there is an
afterlife for all of us,

00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:51.980 align:middle line:84%
and I think that
afterlife is wonderful.

00:06:51.980 --> 00:06:53.780 align:middle line:84%
But I think what's
even more important

00:06:53.780 --> 00:06:55.282 align:middle line:90%
is why I believe that.

00:06:55.282 --> 00:06:56.240 align:middle line:90%
What evidence is there?

00:06:56.240 --> 00:06:57.680 align:middle line:90%
What is that line of thinking?

00:06:57.680 --> 00:06:59.600 align:middle line:90%
What is that chain of evidence?

00:06:59.600 --> 00:07:03.120 align:middle line:84%
What have we consistently
observed in multiple studies,

00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:06.870 align:middle line:84%
including the NDERF study,
that leads me to believe that?

00:07:06.870 --> 00:07:09.140 align:middle line:10%
And I think it's those nine
lines of evidence that,

00:07:09.140 --> 00:07:13.160 align:middle line:10%
to me personally, are
compelling evidence that we all

00:07:13.160 --> 00:07:16.040 align:middle line:10%
are going to have an afterlife,
that that is something that we

00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:17.390 align:middle line:10%
are all going to experience.

00:07:17.390 --> 00:07:19.610 align:middle line:10%
Our consciousness,
who we are, is going

00:07:19.610 --> 00:07:21.440 align:middle line:10%
to survive our bodily death.

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:23.780 align:middle line:10%
And we're going to go on
into an afterlife, which

00:07:23.780 --> 00:07:26.480 align:middle line:10%
so many near-death
experiencers I've heard

00:07:26.480 --> 00:07:29.510 align:middle line:10%
from call it their real home.

00:07:29.510 --> 00:07:31.520 align:middle line:84%
One of the most significant
lines of evidence

00:07:31.520 --> 00:07:33.830 align:middle line:84%
I have that near-death
experiences prove

00:07:33.830 --> 00:07:37.940 align:middle line:84%
the existence of an afterlife
is the out-of-body observations

00:07:37.940 --> 00:07:40.040 align:middle line:84%
that near-death
experiencers make.

00:07:40.040 --> 00:07:43.040 align:middle line:84%
Nearly half of people who
have a near-death experience

00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:44.810 align:middle line:90%
will have an out-of-body state.

00:07:44.810 --> 00:07:46.520 align:middle line:90%
We'll call it an OBE.

00:07:46.520 --> 00:07:49.190 align:middle line:84%
During that time, their
consciousness rises up.

00:07:49.190 --> 00:07:51.470 align:middle line:84%
And usually from an
area above their body,

00:07:51.470 --> 00:07:53.480 align:middle line:84%
they can observe
both their own body--

00:07:53.480 --> 00:07:56.780 align:middle line:84%
often frantic resuscitation
efforts and other earthly

00:07:56.780 --> 00:07:58.550 align:middle line:90%
ongoing events going on--

00:07:58.550 --> 00:08:01.490 align:middle line:84%
again, at a time that they're
often clinically dead.

00:08:01.490 --> 00:08:06.320 align:middle line:84%
Part of my study was to look
at 617 near-death experiences.

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:10.430 align:middle line:84%
We found 287 of those
near-death experiences involved

00:08:10.430 --> 00:08:14.360 align:middle line:84%
observations of earthly
everyday events at this time

00:08:14.360 --> 00:08:16.670 align:middle line:84%
when they were
unconscious or dead.

00:08:16.670 --> 00:08:18.980 align:middle line:84%
And to my considerable
surprise, we

00:08:18.980 --> 00:08:24.118 align:middle line:84%
found that an unbelievable 97.6%
of the time, every observation

00:08:24.118 --> 00:08:25.910 align:middle line:84%
that they were making,
everything that they

00:08:25.910 --> 00:08:29.660 align:middle line:84%
shared in our survey in their
narrative form was realistic.

00:08:29.660 --> 00:08:31.250 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
there was nothing

00:08:31.250 --> 00:08:34.010 align:middle line:84%
that seemed unrealistic
about their observations

00:08:34.010 --> 00:08:37.070 align:middle line:84%
of earthly events to either
the near-death experiencer

00:08:37.070 --> 00:08:41.990 align:middle line:84%
or to myself personally
looking over their narrative.

00:08:41.990 --> 00:08:43.928 align:middle line:84%
The number of people
that described

00:08:43.928 --> 00:08:45.470 align:middle line:84%
a near-death experience
while they're

00:08:45.470 --> 00:08:47.540 align:middle line:90%
undergoing general anesthetic.

00:08:47.540 --> 00:08:49.340 align:middle line:84%
To understand how
amazing that is,

00:08:49.340 --> 00:08:52.590 align:middle line:84%
understand that when you
have a cardiac arrest,

00:08:52.590 --> 00:08:55.190 align:middle line:84%
you have no potential for
a conscious experience.

00:08:55.190 --> 00:08:58.490 align:middle line:84%
But also, when you're
under general anesthesia,

00:08:58.490 --> 00:09:00.290 align:middle line:84%
you're under a blanket
of complete sleep.

00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:03.680 align:middle line:84%
You have no potential to
have any kind of memory,

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.630 align:middle line:84%
any kind of conscious
awareness, because

00:09:05.630 --> 00:09:07.100 align:middle line:90%
of the general anesthesia.

00:09:07.100 --> 00:09:09.700 align:middle line:84%
But put the two
together, if you will,

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:12.320 align:middle line:84%
there's doubly no reason
for you to have any memory

00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:13.880 align:middle line:90%
or any conscious experience.

00:09:13.880 --> 00:09:16.940 align:middle line:84%
And yet, that is when these
near-death experiencers

00:09:16.940 --> 00:09:19.100 align:middle line:90%
describe their experience.

00:09:19.100 --> 00:09:20.930 align:middle line:84%
We know that's true
because they typically

00:09:20.930 --> 00:09:22.880 align:middle line:84%
describe in the
out-of-body state

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:24.590 align:middle line:84%
during their
near-death experience,

00:09:24.590 --> 00:09:26.420 align:middle line:84%
with their consciousness
above the body,

00:09:26.420 --> 00:09:29.300 align:middle line:84%
they see-- and some have
described dramatically--

00:09:29.300 --> 00:09:32.000 align:middle line:84%
their electro cardiogram,
a measure of heart

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.120 align:middle line:90%
electrical activity, flatlining.

00:09:34.120 --> 00:09:37.010 align:middle line:84%
And there is the immediate
frantic resuscitation efforts

00:09:37.010 --> 00:09:39.950 align:middle line:84%
that they watch from their
ringside seat above their body.

00:09:39.950 --> 00:09:41.870 align:middle line:84%
And then as time
goes on, they go on

00:09:41.870 --> 00:09:44.010 align:middle line:84%
and have a typical
near-death experience.

00:09:44.010 --> 00:09:47.450 align:middle line:84%
But in our study, we found
23 near-death experiencers

00:09:47.450 --> 00:09:50.660 align:middle line:84%
that had their experiences
while under general anesthesia.

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:53.970 align:middle line:84%
I compared 33 elements of the
near-death experience to other

00:09:53.970 --> 00:09:54.770 align:middle line:90%
NDEs--

00:09:54.770 --> 00:09:57.320 align:middle line:84%
that being experiences
not associated

00:09:57.320 --> 00:09:59.190 align:middle line:90%
with general anesthesia.

00:09:59.190 --> 00:10:01.520 align:middle line:84%
And the conclusion, the take
home lesson from my study

00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:04.130 align:middle line:84%
was the two groups of
near-death experiences

00:10:04.130 --> 00:10:05.930 align:middle line:90%
are essentially identical.

00:10:05.930 --> 00:10:07.160 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely amazing.

00:10:07.160 --> 00:10:09.290 align:middle line:84%
Near-death experiences
happen, and they

00:10:09.290 --> 00:10:11.850 align:middle line:84%
are typical near-death
experiences,

00:10:11.850 --> 00:10:14.870 align:middle line:84%
even if they occur under
general anesthesia.

00:10:14.870 --> 00:10:17.450 align:middle line:84%
To me personally,
I am astounded when

00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:19.730 align:middle line:84%
I encounter near-death
experiences that

00:10:19.730 --> 00:10:23.570 align:middle line:84%
occur in the blind that
involve vision, but especially

00:10:23.570 --> 00:10:26.510 align:middle line:84%
near-death experiencers
in those born blind.

00:10:26.510 --> 00:10:28.850 align:middle line:84%
I've interviewed at length
a near-death experiencer

00:10:28.850 --> 00:10:30.770 align:middle line:90%
who was born blind.

00:10:30.770 --> 00:10:34.500 align:middle line:84%
Never had any visual perception
during her entire life.

00:10:34.500 --> 00:10:37.880 align:middle line:84%
And yet, when she had a car
accident at the age of 22,

00:10:37.880 --> 00:10:41.030 align:middle line:84%
all of a sudden she had
vision and described

00:10:41.030 --> 00:10:44.090 align:middle line:84%
in great detail what her body
looked like in the emergency

00:10:44.090 --> 00:10:47.930 align:middle line:84%
room table below, went on to
describe a typically highly

00:10:47.930 --> 00:10:49.550 align:middle line:90%
visual experience.

00:10:49.550 --> 00:10:52.280 align:middle line:84%
And again, there's absolutely
no medical explanation

00:10:52.280 --> 00:10:54.200 align:middle line:90%
for this possible.

00:10:54.200 --> 00:10:58.140 align:middle line:84%
In my research, I
found that a fully 96%

00:10:58.140 --> 00:10:59.850 align:middle line:84%
of the time,
near-death experiencers

00:10:59.850 --> 00:11:02.580 align:middle line:84%
described meeting
familiar beings that they

00:11:02.580 --> 00:11:05.820 align:middle line:84%
knew from their earthly life,
that these beings were deceased

00:11:05.820 --> 00:11:08.483 align:middle line:84%
at the time of the
near-death experience.

00:11:08.483 --> 00:11:09.900 align:middle line:10%
And actually what's
interesting is

00:11:09.900 --> 00:11:11.700 align:middle line:10%
the number of
near-death experiences

00:11:11.700 --> 00:11:14.590 align:middle line:10%
where they encountered
somebody who seemed familiar,

00:11:14.590 --> 00:11:16.680 align:middle line:10%
but they didn't know who it was.

00:11:16.680 --> 00:11:18.540 align:middle line:84%
And only when the
near-death experiencer

00:11:18.540 --> 00:11:21.280 align:middle line:84%
looked at old family
portraits, all of a sudden,

00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:23.740 align:middle line:84%
they would go, a-ha,
that's the individual

00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:24.990 align:middle line:90%
from my near-death experience.

00:11:24.990 --> 00:11:28.800 align:middle line:84%
Say a great grandfather, a
great-great grandmother, people

00:11:28.800 --> 00:11:30.580 align:middle line:84%
that they never even
met in their life.

00:11:30.580 --> 00:11:33.570 align:middle line:84%
And yet there, by studying
old family portraits

00:11:33.570 --> 00:11:36.660 align:middle line:84%
later on after their experience,
suddenly connect the dots

00:11:36.660 --> 00:11:41.470 align:middle line:84%
and realize dramatically that
that was who they encountered.

00:11:41.470 --> 00:11:44.580 align:middle line:84%
We found in our study of
near-death experiences

00:11:44.580 --> 00:11:46.420 align:middle line:84%
not only from just
around the world,

00:11:46.420 --> 00:11:47.940 align:middle line:84%
but even in very
different cultures,

00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:50.970 align:middle line:84%
in non-Western cultures,
the core element

00:11:50.970 --> 00:11:54.240 align:middle line:84%
of near-death experience seems
to be basically the same.

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Near-death experiences
are far more similar

00:11:56.610 --> 00:11:58.380 align:middle line:90%
than they are dissimilar.

00:11:58.380 --> 00:12:03.360 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing to think whether
you're an Arab in Saudi Arabia

00:12:03.360 --> 00:12:06.510 align:middle line:84%
or a Hindu in India or a
Christian in the United

00:12:06.510 --> 00:12:10.470 align:middle line:84%
States, the core NDE
experiments, what happens when

00:12:10.470 --> 00:12:14.010 align:middle line:84%
you nearly die, that elements
of the near-death experience

00:12:14.010 --> 00:12:16.080 align:middle line:90%
all seem to be the same.

00:12:16.080 --> 00:12:18.720 align:middle line:84%
This puts me out, if you
will, a little bit on a limb.

00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:21.240 align:middle line:84%
Here I am as a
physician who's actually

00:12:21.240 --> 00:12:24.750 align:middle line:84%
studied near-death experiences
and making an amazing claim

00:12:24.750 --> 00:12:27.450 align:middle line:84%
that the evidence is so
strong that, certainly to me,

00:12:27.450 --> 00:12:29.550 align:middle line:84%
it proves the existence
of an afterlife.

00:12:29.550 --> 00:12:32.850 align:middle line:10%
For thousands of years, the
great religions have said,

00:12:32.850 --> 00:12:35.070 align:middle line:10%
take on faith that we
have life after death.

00:12:35.070 --> 00:12:38.340 align:middle line:10%
Take on faith that there's more
than just what you see and live

00:12:38.340 --> 00:12:40.980 align:middle line:10%
in our earthly existence,
that you are more,

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:42.690 align:middle line:10%
that you are a
magnificent being that

00:12:42.690 --> 00:12:45.060 align:middle line:10%
lives on and on after you die.

00:12:45.060 --> 00:12:47.040 align:middle line:84%
And you know the
incredible thing is?

00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:48.870 align:middle line:84%
For thousands of
years, that message

00:12:48.870 --> 00:12:52.602 align:middle line:84%
of faith in every shred of
research I have is validated.

00:12:52.602 --> 00:12:54.810 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it seems to
be true that there really

00:12:54.810 --> 00:12:58.270 align:middle line:90%
is life after death.

