decided that somehow
they couldn't

00:21:19.570 --> 00:21:22.000 align:middle line:84%
get the defib unit
in there in time,

00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:23.890 align:middle line:90%
and they had a conversation.

00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:27.010 align:middle line:84%
And the conversation
was, why don't you

00:21:27.010 --> 00:21:28.660 align:middle line:90%
try hitting her chest?

00:21:28.660 --> 00:21:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And everybody kind
of separated away

00:21:30.760 --> 00:21:32.620 align:middle line:90%
from the front of the table.

00:21:32.620 --> 00:21:34.178 align:middle line:84%
And he arced his
arm over his head,

00:21:34.178 --> 00:21:36.470 align:middle line:84%
and it came down and pounded
on the center of my chest.

00:21:36.470 --> 00:21:38.560 align:middle line:90%
So I watched that from above.

00:21:38.560 --> 00:21:40.450 align:middle line:84%
And the second time
he did that and arced

00:21:40.450 --> 00:21:45.730 align:middle line:84%
his arm over his head, then my
vision just shot from up above.

00:21:45.730 --> 00:21:47.500 align:middle line:10%
And when I blinked
open my eyes, I

00:21:47.500 --> 00:21:50.500 align:middle line:10%
had the oxygen mask on my
face and I was looking up

00:21:50.500 --> 00:21:52.370 align:middle line:10%
into everybody's faces.

00:21:52.370 --> 00:21:56.595 align:middle line:10%
I had this euphorial
feeling, this absolute thrill

00:21:56.595 --> 00:21:57.970 align:middle line:10%
to be back in my
body and feeling

00:21:57.970 --> 00:22:02.917 align:middle line:10%
so grateful that I was back,
and I wanted to express that.

00:22:02.917 --> 00:22:04.750 align:middle line:10%
So the minute they took
the oxygen mask off,

00:22:04.750 --> 00:22:08.090 align:middle line:10%
I said, oh my god, that was
an incredible experience.

00:22:08.090 --> 00:22:09.770 align:middle line:10%
I was up on the ceiling.

00:22:09.770 --> 00:22:12.880 align:middle line:10%
I watched you all, and
I could see everything

00:22:12.880 --> 00:22:14.590 align:middle line:10%
that was going on and hear you.

00:22:14.590 --> 00:22:16.660 align:middle line:90%
She put the oxygen mask on me.

00:22:16.660 --> 00:22:18.975 align:middle line:84%
He wheeled in that
heart monitor.

00:22:18.975 --> 00:22:20.350 align:middle line:10%
And I started
pointing out people

00:22:20.350 --> 00:22:23.150 align:middle line:10%
and what they had
done while I was dead.

00:22:23.150 --> 00:22:26.930 align:middle line:10%
And you guys were talking,
and you said this to him,

00:22:26.930 --> 00:22:29.020 align:middle line:10%
and he said that to you.

00:22:29.020 --> 00:22:32.890 align:middle line:84%
The orthopedic surgeon
stayed and comforted me,

00:22:32.890 --> 00:22:35.500 align:middle line:84%
and I told them
what had happened.

00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:37.300 align:middle line:10%
So everybody listened.

00:22:37.300 --> 00:22:40.858 align:middle line:10%
But then as I was wheeled up
to my room and after I was

00:22:40.858 --> 00:22:43.150 align:middle line:10%
stabilized-- and this was
the night before the surgery,

00:22:43.150 --> 00:22:44.650 align:middle line:10%
they did the surgery
the next day--

00:22:44.650 --> 00:22:48.880 align:middle line:10%
no one-- no one would talk to
me about it because they knew

00:22:48.880 --> 00:22:52.090 align:middle line:10%
that they had made an error and
what happened caused me to die,

00:22:52.090 --> 00:22:54.500 align:middle line:10%
and they were
afraid of a lawsuit.

00:22:54.500 --> 00:22:57.110 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't talk about
it for about 10 years.

00:22:57.110 --> 00:22:59.230 align:middle line:10%
But finally, a
friend of mine was

00:22:59.230 --> 00:23:02.000 align:middle line:10%
having someone near to her die.

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:04.570 align:middle line:10%
And so it bubbled
up out of me, and I

00:23:04.570 --> 00:23:08.020 align:middle line:10%
realized it was my
reality all these years.

00:23:08.020 --> 00:23:10.840 align:middle line:10%
And I knew the story, but I
needed to talk to other people

00:23:10.840 --> 00:23:13.420 align:middle line:10%
to kind of help them
because it totally

00:23:13.420 --> 00:23:15.590 align:middle line:10%
eliminated my fear of death.

00:23:15.590 --> 00:23:17.830 align:middle line:84%
I don't really want to
be hurt before I die.

00:23:17.830 --> 00:23:20.380 align:middle line:84%
I want to be able
to have it be easy.

00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:25.840 align:middle line:10%
But the actual experience
takes away all fear

00:23:25.840 --> 00:23:27.880 align:middle line:10%
that you have of passing over.

00:23:27.880 --> 00:23:31.970 align:middle line:90%


00:23:31.970 --> 00:23:33.770 align:middle line:84%
>> And then there's
Jenny Sommers,

00:23:33.770 --> 00:23:37.910 align:middle line:84%
a graphic artist with
IBM in Tucson, Arizona.

00:23:37.910 --> 00:23:40.520 align:middle line:84%
As a young woman, Jenny
went to summer camp

00:23:40.520 --> 00:23:42.590 align:middle line:90%
with a number of her friends.

00:23:42.590 --> 00:23:44.810 align:middle line:84%
To play a joke on
the camp counselors,

00:23:44.810 --> 00:23:48.120 align:middle line:84%
Jenny ran into a building
that was under construction

00:23:48.120 --> 00:23:52.820 align:middle line:84%
and fell 15 feet down a hole
designed for a staircase.

00:23:52.820 --> 00:23:57.770 align:middle line:84%
It took rescuers almost an hour
to reach her comatose body.

00:23:57.770 --> 00:24:00.260 align:middle line:84%
By the time they did,
she was in the midst

00:24:00.260 --> 00:24:02.600 align:middle line:90%
of a deep near-death experience.

00:24:02.600 --> 00:24:05.210 align:middle line:84%
>> And evidently, I guess I had
died because they were talking

00:24:05.210 --> 00:24:07.530 align:middle line:90%
as if I couldn't hear them.

00:24:07.530 --> 00:24:11.420 align:middle line:84%
And I started to float
up out of my body,

00:24:11.420 --> 00:24:13.670 align:middle line:90%
and I was encased in this love.

00:24:13.670 --> 00:24:14.940 align:middle line:90%
It was just wonderful.

00:24:14.940 --> 00:24:18.710 align:middle line:84%
And I said, does everyone
get to experience this?

00:24:18.710 --> 00:24:19.620 align:middle line:90%
It's just marvelous.

00:24:19.620 --> 00:24:20.620 align:middle line:90%
And the answer was, yes.

00:24:20.620 --> 00:24:22.170 align:middle line:90%
And I said, even Hitler?

00:24:22.170 --> 00:24:22.970 align:middle line:90%
And, yes.

00:24:22.970 --> 00:24:25.430 align:middle line:10%
And I knew it had to be
true because that love is

00:24:25.430 --> 00:24:28.595 align:middle line:10%
so inclusive and so beyond
anything in this world.

00:24:28.595 --> 00:24:33.200 align:middle line:84%
The next thing I know, I'm
in front of three moving

00:24:33.200 --> 00:24:36.230 align:middle line:90%
kind of blobby shapes.

00:24:36.230 --> 00:24:39.620 align:middle line:84%
And one of them is my
great grandma Julia,

00:24:39.620 --> 00:24:41.613 align:middle line:84%
and she's telling me
I need to go back.

00:24:41.613 --> 00:24:43.280 align:middle line:84%
And they're saying,
you have to go back.

00:24:43.280 --> 00:24:46.140 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, no, I'm
not going to go back.

00:24:46.140 --> 00:24:48.810 align:middle line:84%
So next thing I
know, I'm with Jesus.

00:24:48.810 --> 00:24:51.140 align:middle line:84%
And I kind of feel like I'm
in the principal's office,

00:24:51.140 --> 00:24:52.988 align:middle line:84%
and he's now telling
me, you don't

00:24:52.988 --> 00:24:54.530 align:middle line:84%
have to go back if
you don't want to.

00:24:54.530 --> 00:24:58.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, finally somebody
is listening to me.

00:24:58.770 --> 00:25:02.100 align:middle line:84%
I took back some
of my future events

00:25:02.100 --> 00:25:04.780 align:middle line:84%
that my family was
going to go through.

00:25:04.780 --> 00:25:08.010 align:middle line:84%
And so when I wake up from
the coma, I see my mom.

00:25:08.010 --> 00:25:12.300 align:middle line:84%
I say, mom, mom, you're
going to die in two years.

00:25:12.300 --> 00:25:15.990 align:middle line:84%
Not knowing I was in a
coma, not knowing they

00:25:15.990 --> 00:25:18.450 align:middle line:84%
said I had a 50-50
chance of survival now.

00:25:18.450 --> 00:25:21.642 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't know the hell
that she had been through.

00:25:21.642 --> 00:25:23.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, she told me
that every time I

00:25:23.100 --> 00:25:26.940 align:middle line:84%
would wake up from recovery
and tell the story again,

00:25:26.940 --> 00:25:28.860 align:middle line:90%
I was forgetting more and more.

00:25:28.860 --> 00:25:31.650 align:middle line:84%
So now we're out of the
hospital, we're back home.

00:25:31.650 --> 00:25:34.500 align:middle line:84%
And she has a Raymond
Moody book in her hand,

00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:38.130 align:middle line:84%
and she said, tell me again
about me dying in two years.

00:25:38.130 --> 00:25:40.717 align:middle line:90%
And I said, what?

00:25:40.717 --> 00:25:42.050 align:middle line:90%
And I could see she was serious.

00:25:42.050 --> 00:25:44.740 align:middle line:84%
I said, wait, why are
you asking me that?

00:25:44.740 --> 00:25:46.730 align:middle line:84%
And she said, you told
me that in the hospital

00:25:46.730 --> 00:25:48.063 align:middle line:90%
I was going to die in two years.

00:25:48.063 --> 00:25:49.370 align:middle line:90%
I said, no, I didn't.

00:25:49.370 --> 00:25:51.120 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't believe
she was telling me.

00:25:51.120 --> 00:25:53.100 align:middle line:84%
She closed the
Raymond Moody book.

00:25:53.100 --> 00:25:55.350 align:middle line:84%
She said she never wanted
to talk about it again.

00:25:55.350 --> 00:25:59.380 align:middle line:84%
Go fast forward two
years later, my mom dies.

00:25:59.380 --> 00:26:00.900 align:middle line:84%
She's in a car wreck
with my sister.

00:26:00.900 --> 00:26:03.840 align:middle line:84%
My sister was the driver,
but they got hit head-on.

00:26:03.840 --> 00:26:09.720 align:middle line:84%
And Teresa survives,
but my mom doesn't.

00:26:09.720 --> 00:26:12.540 align:middle line:84%
It's about reconnecting
to who we really are.

00:26:12.540 --> 00:26:16.920 align:middle line:84%
It's a universal mind
that we reconnect to.

00:26:16.920 --> 00:26:20.750 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like here we're
unplugged from our source,

00:26:20.750 --> 00:26:23.790 align:middle line:84%
and we try to take
our plug and plug it

00:26:23.790 --> 00:26:26.017 align:middle line:90%
into each other and things.

00:26:26.017 --> 00:26:27.600 align:middle line:84%
This person is going
to make me happy.

00:26:27.600 --> 00:26:29.400 align:middle line:84%
This car is going
to make me happy.

00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:33.240 align:middle line:84%
And we keep trying to draw
our energy from people,

00:26:33.240 --> 00:26:35.640 align:middle line:90%
things, this dimension.

00:26:35.640 --> 00:26:39.420 align:middle line:84%
And every time we take
that plug and we connect it

00:26:39.420 --> 00:26:42.960 align:middle line:84%
back to our source,
then we become full

00:26:42.960 --> 00:26:44.370 align:middle line:90%
and then we become connected.

00:26:44.370 --> 00:26:48.330 align:middle line:84%
And so now I realize I don't
need these outside things,

00:26:48.330 --> 00:26:51.390 align:middle line:84%
but I can be that light in
memory, that energy that

00:26:51.390 --> 00:26:53.850 align:middle line:84%
reminds people to not
plug into each other

00:26:53.850 --> 00:26:56.382 align:middle line:90%
but to plug into God.

00:26:56.382 --> 00:27:01.706 align:middle line:90%


