Did your life flash
before your eyes?

00:30:26.040 --> 00:30:26.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Definitely.

00:30:26.560 --> 00:30:27.360 align:middle line:90%
But I was small.

00:30:27.360 --> 00:30:28.380 align:middle line:90%
I was seven years old.

00:30:28.380 --> 00:30:29.297 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you were seven.

00:30:29.297 --> 00:30:30.352 align:middle line:90%
>> Seven years old.

00:30:30.352 --> 00:30:31.950 align:middle line:10%
>> And it's just
this endless thing,

00:30:31.950 --> 00:30:35.280 align:middle line:10%
just like here and right now,
like here in this interview,

00:30:35.280 --> 00:30:36.930 align:middle line:10%
and different stages.

00:30:36.930 --> 00:30:38.878 align:middle line:10%
And it's like the play
is always different.

00:30:38.878 --> 00:30:40.170 align:middle line:90%
It's always a different script.

00:30:40.170 --> 00:30:41.910 align:middle line:90%
It's always a different movie.

00:30:41.910 --> 00:30:45.008 align:middle line:10%
But it's the same soul
always going through.

00:30:45.008 --> 00:30:46.050 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I believe.

00:30:46.050 --> 00:30:49.494 align:middle line:90%


00:30:49.494 --> 00:30:51.954 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30:51.954 --> 00:31:01.310 align:middle line:90%


00:31:01.310 --> 00:31:04.790 align:middle line:84%
>> I arrived at Dr. Raymond
Moody's house in Deep South

00:31:04.790 --> 00:31:05.590 align:middle line:90%
Alabama.

00:31:05.590 --> 00:31:09.010 align:middle line:90%


00:31:09.010 --> 00:31:10.653 align:middle line:90%
Raymond, how's it going?

00:31:10.653 --> 00:31:11.559 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, Paul.

00:31:11.559 --> 00:31:13.371 align:middle line:90%
Good to see you, man.

00:31:13.371 --> 00:31:14.277 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey, man.

00:31:14.277 --> 00:31:15.173 align:middle line:90%
>> How you been?

00:31:15.173 --> 00:31:15.536 align:middle line:90%
>> Good.

00:31:15.536 --> 00:31:17.369 align:middle line:84%
I'm here to talk to you
about the afterlife.

00:31:17.369 --> 00:31:18.169 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah?

00:31:18.169 --> 00:31:19.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's my
favorite subject.

00:31:19.610 --> 00:31:20.410 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, let's do it.

00:31:20.410 --> 00:31:22.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Let's go talk about it.

00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:26.480 align:middle line:84%
>> In the early '70s, Dr. Moody,
then a philosophy professor

00:31:26.480 --> 00:31:28.790 align:middle line:84%
trained at the
University of Virginia,

00:31:28.790 --> 00:31:32.570 align:middle line:84%
began to explore the stories
of people who had almost died

00:31:32.570 --> 00:31:36.390 align:middle line:84%
and crossed the line
into a heavenly realm.

00:31:36.390 --> 00:31:39.600 align:middle line:84%
These stories have been told
throughout human history,

00:31:39.600 --> 00:31:43.160 align:middle line:84%
but Dr. Moody was the first
to dissect them and discover

00:31:43.160 --> 00:31:45.330 align:middle line:90%
their similarities.

00:31:45.330 --> 00:31:48.500 align:middle line:84%
He called them
near-death experiences.

00:31:48.500 --> 00:31:51.740 align:middle line:84%
When he wrote about these
in a book "Life After Life,"

00:31:51.740 --> 00:31:54.890 align:middle line:84%
the field of near-death
studies began.

00:31:54.890 --> 00:31:57.290 align:middle line:84%
I have written four
books with Raymond.

00:31:57.290 --> 00:32:00.830 align:middle line:84%
I even helped him move into
his home here in rural Alabama.

00:32:00.830 --> 00:32:03.140 align:middle line:84%
So I felt very comfortable
interviewing him

00:32:03.140 --> 00:32:04.640 align:middle line:90%
in his living room.

00:32:04.640 --> 00:32:06.830 align:middle line:84%
But even as well
as I know Raymond,

00:32:06.830 --> 00:32:09.860 align:middle line:84%
I was surprised by
some of his answers.

00:32:09.860 --> 00:32:12.490 align:middle line:84%
You've had your own
near-death experience.

00:32:12.490 --> 00:32:15.300 align:middle line:84%
And based on those
two things, the fact

00:32:15.300 --> 00:32:16.960 align:middle line:84%
that you've heard
all these stories

00:32:16.960 --> 00:32:20.540 align:middle line:84%
and you have your own story
to tell, what do you think

00:32:20.540 --> 00:32:22.450 align:middle line:90%
happens when we die?

00:32:22.450 --> 00:32:25.120 align:middle line:90%


00:32:25.120 --> 00:32:30.820 align:middle line:84%
>> What I think happens
when we die is that we enter

00:32:30.820 --> 00:32:37.270 align:middle line:84%
into another state of
existence or another state

00:32:37.270 --> 00:32:43.270 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness that is so
extraordinarily different from

00:32:43.270 --> 00:32:48.340 align:middle line:84%
the spatial and temporal frame
of reality in which we exist

00:32:48.340 --> 00:32:53.200 align:middle line:84%
in the physical world that the
language we have is not yet

00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:56.380 align:middle line:84%
adequate to describe this
other state of existence

00:32:56.380 --> 00:32:59.270 align:middle line:90%
or consciousness.

00:32:59.270 --> 00:33:03.220 align:middle line:84%
>> When we leave our mortal
body, how do we leave it?

00:33:03.220 --> 00:33:04.420 align:middle line:90%
What do we look like?

00:33:04.420 --> 00:33:07.480 align:middle line:84%
>> People say that in the
realm of existence they enter

00:33:07.480 --> 00:33:11.410 align:middle line:84%
into upon the point of death
that there is no such thing

00:33:11.410 --> 00:33:14.950 align:middle line:84%
as physicality as we
experience in this realm.

00:33:14.950 --> 00:33:18.070 align:middle line:84%
It's not that they
have a physical body.

00:33:18.070 --> 00:33:20.710 align:middle line:84%
It's rather that they have
some other sort of vehicle,

00:33:20.710 --> 00:33:23.950 align:middle line:84%
which they find it very
difficult to describe,

00:33:23.950 --> 00:33:29.170 align:middle line:84%
but that it does have a form,
that it carries a personality,

00:33:29.170 --> 00:33:33.820 align:middle line:84%
but that it's just entirely
impossible to describe it

00:33:33.820 --> 00:33:40.390 align:middle line:84%
in terms of or analogously to
the kind of body that we have.

00:33:40.390 --> 00:33:44.920 align:middle line:84%
I've heard it characterized as
a spiritual body, for example.

00:33:44.920 --> 00:33:48.820 align:middle line:84%
That's a term that I hear
from a lot of people.

00:33:48.820 --> 00:33:51.380 align:middle line:84%
>> So when they come
back, they're changed.

00:33:51.380 --> 00:33:52.780 align:middle line:90%
They're transformed.

00:33:52.780 --> 00:33:55.140 align:middle line:84%
>> There are a number of
transformations we see with

00:33:55.140 --> 00:33:58.020 align:middle line:84%
people who come back from
near-death experiences.

00:33:58.020 --> 00:34:00.060 align:middle line:84%
The most prominent
one is that whatever

00:34:00.060 --> 00:34:03.480 align:middle line:84%
they had been chasing
before, whether knowledge

00:34:03.480 --> 00:34:07.570 align:middle line:84%
or fame or power or money or
any of these other things,

00:34:07.570 --> 00:34:09.300 align:middle line:84%
that when they
come back, they say

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:13.469 align:middle line:84%
that the most important thing
we can do while we're alive

00:34:13.469 --> 00:34:17.790 align:middle line:90%
is to learn how to love.

00:34:17.790 --> 00:34:20.580 align:middle line:84%
>> How has this knowledge
affected your life?

00:34:20.580 --> 00:34:25.199 align:middle line:84%
>> The most powerful one to
me has been that it really has

00:34:25.199 --> 00:34:28.110 align:middle line:84%
convinced me of the
importance of love,

00:34:28.110 --> 00:34:32.219 align:middle line:84%
and I try in every day
to be loving to people.

00:34:32.219 --> 00:34:36.060 align:middle line:84%
I genuinely do try in my
day-to-day interactions

00:34:36.060 --> 00:34:40.260 align:middle line:84%
with people, that I try to keep
in mind that I will be seeing

00:34:40.260 --> 00:34:43.920 align:middle line:84%
this again and that I will
be seeing this event not

00:34:43.920 --> 00:34:47.100 align:middle line:84%
from the way I'm seeing
it now through these eyes,

00:34:47.100 --> 00:34:49.469 align:middle line:84%
but that I will be
seeing this event

00:34:49.469 --> 00:34:55.800 align:middle line:84%
through the eyes of the people
with whom I've interacted.

00:34:55.800 --> 00:34:58.800 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you think the world
would change if you were able

00:34:58.800 --> 00:35:00.840 align:middle line:84%
to prove that there
was an afterlife?

00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:04.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Many people get to thinking
about this, and they think, oh,

00:35:04.380 --> 00:35:07.630 align:middle line:84%
if that were the case, then
we'd all love each other.

00:35:07.630 --> 00:35:10.020 align:middle line:84%
And there would be
nirvana, and there wouldn't

00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:14.320 align:middle line:90%
be any problems in the world.

00:35:14.320 --> 00:35:17.250 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think it
would bring people

00:35:17.250 --> 00:35:21.010 align:middle line:84%
to a state of complete love and
make everybody saints and so

00:35:21.010 --> 00:35:21.810 align:middle line:90%
on.

00:35:21.810 --> 00:35:23.550 align:middle line:90%
I honestly don't accept that.

00:35:23.550 --> 00:35:27.270 align:middle line:84%
But there is one thing
that I am absolutely

00:35:27.270 --> 00:35:32.950 align:middle line:84%
sure that a rational proof
of life after death would do,

00:35:32.950 --> 00:35:35.670 align:middle line:84%
and that would be that
it would fundamentally

00:35:35.670 --> 00:35:40.440 align:middle line:84%
alter the structure
of the human mind.

00:35:40.440 --> 00:35:43.380 align:middle line:84%
If we could have a rational
proof of life after death,

00:35:43.380 --> 00:35:45.570 align:middle line:84%
then human beings
would never again

00:35:45.570 --> 00:35:50.940 align:middle line:84%
be the same because the entire
structure of our cognitive mind

00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:53.910 align:middle line:90%
would be expanded.

00:35:53.910 --> 00:35:57.960 align:middle line:84%
What I can honestly tell you
from the bottom of my heart

00:35:57.960 --> 00:36:01.350 align:middle line:84%
is that I accept
that there is a God

00:36:01.350 --> 00:36:03.360 align:middle line:84%
and I have a
relationship with God

00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:06.000 align:middle line:84%
and I talk with
Him all the time.

00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:09.780 align:middle line:84%
What I honestly don't know yet
from the rational point of view

00:36:09.780 --> 00:36:14.260 align:middle line:84%
is whether life after death
is in His plan or not.

00:36:14.260 --> 00:36:17.580 align:middle line:84%
And it may well be, if you
think about it, that God

00:36:17.580 --> 00:36:21.030 align:middle line:84%
has something in
mind for us that

00:36:21.030 --> 00:36:23.520 align:middle line:84%
is even more
remarkable than what we

00:36:23.520 --> 00:36:25.740 align:middle line:90%
might call a life after death.

00:36:25.740 --> 00:36:27.920 align:middle line:90%
In other words, I love God.

00:36:27.920 --> 00:36:30.630 align:middle line:84%
I have a trusting
relationship with God.

00:36:30.630 --> 00:36:34.065 align:middle line:84%
He hasn't told me anything
yet about an afterlife.

00:36:34.065 --> 00:36:38.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to
have to wait and see.

00:36:38.360 --> 00:36:40.370 align:middle line:84%
>> The next day,
I went back to Dr.

00:36:40.370 --> 00:36:43.870 align:middle line:84%
Moody's to talk to him about
his next field of study--

00:36:43.870 --> 00:36:46.760 align:middle line:90%
shared death experiences.

00:36:46.760 --> 00:36:50.180 align:middle line:84%
He feels this subject may
provide the best answer yet

00:36:50.180 --> 00:36:53.960 align:middle line:84%
to the question, what
happens when we die?

00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:56.510 align:middle line:84%
Simply stated, shared
death experiences

00:36:56.510 --> 00:36:59.600 align:middle line:84%
take place when
bystanders at the deathbed

00:36:59.600 --> 00:37:03.380 align:middle line:84%
have the same experience
as the person who is dying.

00:37:03.380 --> 00:37:05.870 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they say that
they went up a tunnel

00:37:05.870 --> 00:37:08.750 align:middle line:84%
or had a life review
with the dying person.

00:37:08.750 --> 00:37:12.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Now the implication of
this, if you think about it,

00:37:12.200 --> 00:37:15.590 align:middle line:84%
is that this really does
throw a monkey wrench

00:37:15.590 --> 00:37:18.530 align:middle line:84%
in the traditional way of
debating about near-death

00:37:18.530 --> 00:37:20.030 align:middle line:90%
experiences.

00:37:20.030 --> 00:37:24.050 align:middle line:84%
Because what the
physiologists tell

00:37:24.050 --> 00:37:28.580 align:middle line:84%
us, who say that these
experiences are hallucinatory,

00:37:28.580 --> 00:37:34.100 align:middle line:84%
is that as the person is
dying, the oxygen supply

00:37:34.100 --> 00:37:36.170 align:middle line:90%
to their brain is lowered.

00:37:36.170 --> 00:37:40.920 align:middle line:84%
And hence, they have these
hallucinatory effects.

00:37:40.920 --> 00:37:44.000 align:middle line:84%
But if that's true, why
would the bystanders

00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:45.660 align:middle line:84%
have the same kind
of experience?

00:37:45.660 --> 00:37:46.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:37:46.460 --> 00:37:47.870 align:middle line:90%
Well, why would they?

00:37:47.870 --> 00:37:50.220 align:middle line:84%
>> That's very
difficult to explain.

00:37:50.220 --> 00:37:56.480 align:middle line:84%
And I think that once these
findings come out and are

00:37:56.480 --> 00:37:59.330 align:middle line:84%
thoroughly understood
by the public,

00:37:59.330 --> 00:38:03.230 align:middle line:84%
we're going to be into
an entirely new dimension

00:38:03.230 --> 00:38:06.500 align:middle line:84%
of discussing
near-death experiences

00:38:06.500 --> 00:38:10.280 align:middle line:84%
because that old
stand-by, that, oh,

00:38:10.280 --> 00:38:14.210 align:middle line:84%
this is just hallucinations
caused by brain damage, that's

00:38:14.210 --> 00:38:19.230 align:middle line:84%
out the window with these
empathic death experiences.

00:38:19.230 --> 00:38:21.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Now if you don't
mind me saying this,

00:38:21.390 --> 00:38:25.250 align:middle line:84%
you and your family had a shared
death experience at the bedside

00:38:25.250 --> 00:38:26.510 align:middle line:90%
of your mother.

00:38:26.510 --> 00:38:27.810 align:middle line:90%
>> I did indeed.

00:38:27.810 --> 00:38:32.390 align:middle line:84%
In 1994, when my
mother was dying,

00:38:32.390 --> 00:38:37.670 align:middle line:84%
my wife and I and my sisters
and one of my brother in-laws

00:38:37.670 --> 00:38:43.550 align:middle line:84%
were there, and all had
astonishing experiences

00:38:43.550 --> 00:38:46.010 align:middle line:90%
at the moment my mother died.

00:38:46.010 --> 00:38:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it's one of the
most exciting fields to study.

00:38:48.860 --> 00:38:50.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yes, Paul.

00:38:50.120 --> 00:38:51.570 align:middle line:84%
>> The study of
afterlife studies,

00:38:51.570 --> 00:38:53.320 align:middle line:84%
I think this is one
of the most exciting--

00:38:53.320 --> 00:38:57.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Paul, this is the new
frontier of knowledge.

00:38:57.050 --> 00:39:00.740 align:middle line:84%
Because now we have
not only this awareness

00:39:00.740 --> 00:39:04.010 align:middle line:84%
that these near-death
experiences are not

00:39:04.010 --> 00:39:07.850 align:middle line:84%
confined to the people who
almost die, but kind of leak

00:39:07.850 --> 00:39:13.370 align:middle line:84%
out by whatever unknown means
to the people standing around.

00:39:13.370 --> 00:39:20.460 align:middle line:84%
And it is a very paradoxical
and astonishing thing

00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:23.150 align:middle line:90%
to wonder what is going on here.

00:39:23.150 --> 00:39:26.750 align:middle line:84%
>> "Men love to wonder,"
said Ralph Waldo Emerson,

00:39:26.750 --> 00:39:29.210 align:middle line:84%
"and that is the
seed of science."

00:39:29.210 --> 00:39:31.070 align:middle line:84%
I am reminded of
that quote whenever

00:39:31.070 --> 00:39:32.760 align:middle line:90%
I am with Raymond Moody.

00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:34.880 align:middle line:84%
For half of his
life and counting,

00:39:34.880 --> 00:39:38.280 align:middle line:84%
the good doctor has pursued
the big question of religion,

00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:40.220 align:middle line:90%
science, and philosophy--

00:39:40.220 --> 00:39:43.070 align:middle line:90%
what happens when we die?

00:39:43.070 --> 00:39:46.040 align:middle line:84%
But there are people out
there, millions of them,

00:39:46.040 --> 00:39:49.040 align:middle line:84%
of all races, creeds,
colors, and religion

00:39:49.040 --> 00:39:51.590 align:middle line:84%
who don't need a
scientific answer.

00:39:51.590 --> 00:39:52.970 align:middle line:90%
They know from experience.

00:39:52.970 --> 00:39:57.398 align:middle line:90%


00:39:57.398 --> 00:39:59.858 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:59.858 --> 00:40:06.270 align:middle line:90%


00:40:06.270 --> 00:40:08.130 align:middle line:84%
I traveled to the
Pacific Northwest

00:40:08.130 --> 00:40:10.500 align:middle line:90%
to visit Galen Dean Loven.

00:40:10.500 --> 00:40:13.650 align:middle line:84%
At the age of 11, Galen
took it upon himself

00:40:13.650 --> 00:40:17.460 align:middle line:84%
to prove to a neighbor that
gasoline burns on water.

00:40:17.460 --> 00:40:21.660 align:middle line:84%
He filled a 5-gallon gas can
from the family farm's gas tank

00:40:21.660 --> 00:40:24.540 align:middle line:84%
and went down to a nearby
creek to make his point.

00:40:24.540 --> 00:40:28.860 align:middle line:84%
>> I was standing on these
two logs pouring the gasoline

00:40:28.860 --> 00:40:35.300 align:middle line:84%
upstream, so the gasoline
is flowing underneath me.

00:40:35.300 --> 00:40:37.650 align:middle line:84%
And I look over, and
there is my friend

00:40:37.650 --> 00:40:41.050 align:middle line:84%
approaching the creek
with a lit match.

00:40:41.050 --> 00:40:44.850 align:middle line:90%
And the look on his face was--

00:40:44.850 --> 00:40:46.080 align:middle line:90%
I would say horror.

00:40:46.080 --> 00:40:49.220 align:middle line:84%
He was doing something he
didn't really mean to do,

00:40:49.220 --> 00:40:50.700 align:middle line:90%
but could not do.

00:40:50.700 --> 00:40:53.910 align:middle line:84%
>> In a hot second, Galen
was covered by gasoline

00:40:53.910 --> 00:40:55.900 align:middle line:90%
and engulfed in flames.

00:40:55.900 --> 00:40:59.130 align:middle line:84%
The pain was so intense that
young Galen could feel nothing.

00:40:59.130 --> 00:41:01.080 align:middle line:84%
He collapsed into
the water, where

00:41:01.080 --> 00:41:04.020 align:middle line:84%
his voyage to the
other side began.

00:41:04.020 --> 00:41:06.850 align:middle line:84%
>> My next awareness is I'm
horizontal with my hands

00:41:06.850 --> 00:41:09.220 align:middle line:90%
by my side in a funnel.

00:41:09.220 --> 00:41:12.150 align:middle line:84%
It was not really a tunnel,
but it was a funnel.

00:41:12.150 --> 00:41:16.120 align:middle line:84%
And the inclination of the
sides was not that great,

00:41:16.120 --> 00:41:18.000 align:middle line:90%
but it was obvious.

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:21.450 align:middle line:84%
And I was horizontal dead
center, and I was moving along.

00:41:21.450 --> 00:41:23.820 align:middle line:90%
And I was aware of my body.

00:41:23.820 --> 00:41:25.860 align:middle line:90%
My whole body was there.

00:41:25.860 --> 00:41:32.460 align:middle line:84%
I could look and see,
and it was physical, OK?

00:41:32.460 --> 00:41:34.650 align:middle line:90%
It was very physical.

00:41:34.650 --> 00:41:37.440 align:middle line:90%
And inside the cone was--

00:41:37.440 --> 00:41:40.200 align:middle line:84%
it wasn't a vacuum,
but it wasn't anything

00:41:40.200 --> 00:41:42.180 align:middle line:84%
in particular other
than something.

00:41:42.180 --> 00:41:45.850 align:middle line:84%
I knew outside of this funnel
there was more substance.

00:41:45.850 --> 00:41:49.545 align:middle line:84%
It felt more solid on the
outside of the funnel.

00:41:49.545 --> 00:41:51.465 align:middle line:84%
I'm moving along a bit
and then look ahead,

00:41:51.465 --> 00:41:53.970 align:middle line:84%
and I see this
little tiny pinpoint

00:41:53.970 --> 00:41:55.670 align:middle line:90%
of light, a little white light.

00:41:55.670 --> 00:41:58.980 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, my
speed really picks up.

00:41:58.980 --> 00:42:01.380 align:middle line:90%
So I'm accelerating like crazy.

00:42:01.380 --> 00:42:04.140 align:middle line:84%
It's not that I reach a fast
speed and stay at that speed,

00:42:04.140 --> 00:42:06.720 align:middle line:84%
but every millisecond, I'm
moving faster and faster

00:42:06.720 --> 00:42:08.160 align:middle line:90%
and faster and faster.

00:42:08.160 --> 00:42:10.530 align:middle line:84%
As I'm doing that, the
sides of the funnel

00:42:10.530 --> 00:42:11.880 align:middle line:90%
are expanding away from me.

00:42:11.880 --> 00:42:13.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm still dead center.

00:42:13.660 --> 00:42:14.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm still physical.

00:42:14.730 --> 00:42:16.590 align:middle line:90%
I'm still able to look around.

00:42:16.590 --> 00:42:20.400 align:middle line:84%
And this feeling of excitement,
